    },
    {
     "text": "::pic:borders\\borderv_8x50",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 11160,
      "top": 5160,
      "height": 4800,
      "width": 120
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 8.25,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "::pic:misc\\info1_32x32",
     "color": "rgb(255,0,0)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2040,
      "top": 1200,
      "height": 480,
      "width": 480
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 8.25,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "It is not possible to screen clearly within DDT which port is UDP port, and which port is TCP port",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2760,
      "top": 1320,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 9840
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "In order to differenciate TCP and UDP ports, you have to use the TCP and UDP counters",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2760,
      "top": 1680,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 9840
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "TCP ports are screened first, followed by UDP ports",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2760,
      "top": 2040,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 9840
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "Example: If TCP port counter indicates 3 and UDP port counter indicates 2, the first 3 ports are TCP, the 2 last ports are UDP",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2760,
      "top": 2400,
      "height": 600,
      "width": 9840
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "TCP Port number",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2760,
      "top": 3240,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 2400
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "UDP Port number",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 2760,
      "top": 3720,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 2400
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    }
   ],
